          <p class="book-info__copy__description-content">"Atomic Habits" is a self-help book written by James Clear, focusing on the science and psychology behind habit formation and how to make small changes that yield remarkable results. Clear introduces the concept of "atomic habits," which are tiny changes that have a significant impact when practiced consistently over time. He outlines a practical framework for building and breaking habits, emphasizing the importance of cues, cravings, responses, and rewards. Through real-life examples, research-based insights, and actionable strategies, Clear provides readers with a roadmap for transforming their habits</p>
